WEBVTT

00:02.336 --> 00:04.827
JULIA:
Chester's Mill is a place like any other.

00:05.005 --> 00:06.836
At least it used to be.

00:07.007 --> 00:10.716
Until we were cut off from the rest
of the world by a mysterious dome.

00:14.681 --> 00:18.765
Invisible, indestructible,
and completely inescapable.

00:18.936 --> 00:20.267
We're trapped.

00:20.938 --> 00:23.429
JULIA: We don't know where
it came from or why it's here.

00:23.607 --> 00:25.723
But now that we 're all trapped
under the dome together,

00:25.901 --> 00:27.482
none of our secrets are safe.

00:27.653 --> 00:31.566
- It's the pink stars.
JOE: They're making constellations.

00:31.740 --> 00:32.980
What does it mean?

00:33.534 --> 00:35.399
JULIA:
Peter got in over his head

00:35.577 --> 00:38.364
and forced you to kill him
to defend yourself.

00:38.789 --> 00:40.620
I found this
life insurance policy today.

00:40.791 --> 00:43.624
This would be void
if he committed suicide.

00:43.794 --> 00:45.580
BARBIE: Hello, Max.
- For the past eight days,

00:45.754 --> 00:46.789
I've been watching you.

00:47.422 --> 00:49.708
Anything bad happens to me,
your secrets still come out.

00:49.883 --> 00:51.259
AGATHA:
That's my daughter Maxine.

00:51.426 --> 00:52.711
[GUN COCKS]

00:52.886 --> 00:54.547
Now do me a favor
and drop that gun.

00:56.098 --> 00:59.056
- Agatha!
- Please.

00:59.226 --> 01:00.591
[GASPING]

01:02.437 --> 01:04.302
It's amazing.

01:04.773 --> 01:06.889
It's still just a barn, Galileo.

01:07.067 --> 01:09.604
ANGIE: So all the dots in that egg
made constellations.

01:09.778 --> 01:11.439
But what does that mean?

01:11.613 --> 01:14.446
Maybe the dome's trying
to communicate.

01:15.867 --> 01:20.236
It stopped the riots with the rain,
made us babble about pink stars.

01:21.665 --> 01:23.951
I wonder what it's trying
to tell us now.

01:27.671 --> 01:29.411
I don't know.

01:30.591 --> 01:35.051
But these four stars aren't
part of any constellation.

01:35.596 --> 01:36.836
I think they're us.

01:38.265 --> 01:40.551
JUNIOR:
What's this guy have to do with it?

01:43.353 --> 01:48.222
Hey, it changed color overnight
from green to clear.

01:48.400 --> 01:51.437
- You can see wings now.
- It's a monarch.

01:51.612 --> 01:55.275
It's gonna hatch into a butterfly.
It's pretty rad.

01:55.449 --> 01:57.656
It's not rad, it's insane!

01:57.826 --> 02:01.239
We're like the guardians of some
secret cosmic mystery.

02:03.874 --> 02:05.205
It's too much, it's too much.

02:07.336 --> 02:09.201
We've gotta tell somebody.

02:09.379 --> 02:12.963
The dome's been pretty clear about not
wanting anyone else to know about it.

02:13.133 --> 02:16.091
When Dodee snuck in here, she got
zapped and wound up in the hospital.

02:17.804 --> 02:19.510
We could tell Julia.

02:20.223 --> 02:21.633
When she touched this thing,

02:21.808 --> 02:24.925
she said my ghost told her
that the monarch will be crowned.

02:25.103 --> 02:28.687
Maybe she's not one of us,
but she might have some answers.

02:28.857 --> 02:29.892
JUNIOR:
He's right.

02:30.776 --> 02:33.643
That thing's gonna hatch,
and when it does,

02:33.820 --> 02:37.938
maybe it will lead us to something,
or someone.

02:38.575 --> 02:40.190
Like the monarch's a person.

02:41.703 --> 02:43.318
Like a king maybe.

02:43.497 --> 02:45.237
Who might be able
to bring the dome down.

02:45.415 --> 02:49.875
All right, so the dome trusts Julia.

02:50.045 --> 02:51.376
Joe, go tell her.

03:01.932 --> 03:03.923
I just wanna make sure
we're on the same page.

03:04.101 --> 03:06.558
So you, Duke Perkins
and Reverend Coggins

03:06.728 --> 03:08.969
conspired to acquire
a vast amount of propane?

03:09.147 --> 03:11.479
Yeah, we bought propane
off the books.

03:11.650 --> 03:13.732
But only to keep this town afloat.

03:13.902 --> 03:17.736
By selling it to Maxine Seagrave,
a drug dealer?

03:17.906 --> 03:19.567
But you kept some of it
in your warehouse.

03:19.741 --> 03:22.403
And you can thank the Lord
that we did.

03:22.577 --> 03:29.073
Because right now in the middle
of this nightmare, the lights are on.

03:29.251 --> 03:33.244
Because your generator
is running using my propane.

03:33.422 --> 03:35.708
The diner's open
because of my propane.

03:35.882 --> 03:38.999
We're setting up irrigation for crops,
bartering systems.

03:39.177 --> 03:44.092
Hell, Chester's Mill mayjust stay alive
because of my propane.

03:46.309 --> 03:48.140
You think I'm a crook?

03:49.896 --> 03:51.727
I think I'm owed a damn parade.

03:51.898 --> 03:55.356
You know, it doesn't change the fact
that if this dome hadn't come down,

03:55.527 --> 03:57.859
you'd be in jail.

03:58.029 --> 04:00.441
I'd say it saved your ass, Big Jim.

04:01.992 --> 04:03.528
So go ahead.

04:04.411 --> 04:07.448
Charge me with conspiracy
to keep the lights on.

04:09.166 --> 04:14.456
Or you can go after a real criminal.

04:15.547 --> 04:16.832
And who might that be?

04:17.007 --> 04:20.090
Someone who's a real mystery
in this town.

04:20.260 --> 04:21.966
A man who just got here.

04:23.305 --> 04:25.296
Who's only out for himself.

04:26.183 --> 04:30.392
And isn't shy about
letting people know it.

04:41.406 --> 04:45.615
- How was the couch?
- Lonely.

04:47.537 --> 04:49.573
So was the bed.

04:49.748 --> 04:51.534
Do you want me to leave?

04:53.627 --> 04:55.788
I want you to take me
to Peter's grave.

04:59.174 --> 05:03.258
For us to move forward,
I need closure. I think you do too.

05:04.054 --> 05:09.390
So, yeah,
I need to see Peter's grave.

05:21.738 --> 05:23.694
I'll go get dressed.

05:30.580 --> 05:32.081
LINDA:
You want me to go after Barbie?

05:32.249 --> 05:35.082
- What did he ever do?
- Wake up, Linda.

05:35.252 --> 05:38.244
Barbie wasn't just passing through
Chester's Mill.

05:38.421 --> 05:40.377
He was here
working for Max Seagrave.

05:40.549 --> 05:43.086
- He was?
- As her gambling enforcer.

05:43.260 --> 05:46.752
He was here putting the screws
to people in this town, our town.

05:48.306 --> 05:52.595
- No, this sounds--
- Crazy? Till it's true.

05:52.769 --> 05:55.636
Here's a name you haven't heard
in a while. Peter Shumway.

05:56.273 --> 05:58.434
He was up to his eyeballs
in debt to Max.

05:58.608 --> 06:01.850
Barbie was with him the day the dome
came down, and guess what.

06:02.654 --> 06:05.361
Haven't heard a peep
from old Peter since.

06:12.038 --> 06:16.873
Some people have secrets
you couldn't imagine.

06:20.714 --> 06:24.673
- What about you?
- I'm an open book.

06:26.136 --> 06:27.626
[DOORBELL RINGS]

06:27.804 --> 06:29.305
I got it.

06:35.020 --> 06:36.055
Can I help you?

06:36.479 --> 06:38.561
Right now
you can't even help yourself.

06:46.781 --> 06:48.362
[COUGHS]

07:03.381 --> 07:04.917
BARBIE:
Julia!

07:07.719 --> 07:08.879
Hold on.

07:10.805 --> 07:12.887
- Linda, are you there?
LINDA [OVER RADIO]: I’m here.

07:13.058 --> 07:15.014
- Julia's been shot.
- What?

07:15.185 --> 07:17.016
She answered the door
and somebody shot her.

07:17.187 --> 07:18.893
- Who?
- I don't know!

07:19.856 --> 07:21.141
If you can believe him.

07:25.528 --> 07:28.986
Linda, listen, I can't drive and keep her
from bleeding out at the same time.

07:29.157 --> 07:30.522
I need someone to give me a ride.

07:30.700 --> 07:35.285
- I'll be right there, Barbie.
- Linda, think.

07:36.539 --> 07:37.870
Think.

07:42.671 --> 07:45.538
- You hungry?
- Yeah.

07:45.715 --> 07:49.628
Well, our chickens are still laying eggs.
I can scramble some up.

07:52.305 --> 07:54.045
Can you believe it, Angie?

07:55.141 --> 07:58.304
Uh, no, it's all been pretty crazy.

07:58.853 --> 07:59.888
I mean us.

08:01.564 --> 08:04.306
|... |, uh...

08:05.986 --> 08:08.523
I never thought fate was real.

08:08.697 --> 08:12.064
That there was this plan.

08:12.826 --> 08:15.488
- But now it's undeniable.
- What are you talking about?

08:15.662 --> 08:19.575
The way our lives are braided together,
and they will be forever.

08:21.710 --> 08:22.790
What? Are you insane?

08:22.961 --> 08:23.996
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

08:24.170 --> 08:26.252
You kept me prisoner, okay?
I almost died down there!

08:26.423 --> 08:28.505
But you didn't.

08:28.675 --> 08:31.212
We're both alive
and we're here right now.

08:31.678 --> 08:33.760
It is the four of us
who are connected.

08:33.930 --> 08:36.967
It is not about you and me.
It will never be about you--

08:37.142 --> 08:38.632
- I don't believe you.
- Believe it!

08:38.810 --> 08:41.426
We will never be together!

08:41.604 --> 08:45.267
And if somehow we make this dome
come down, then I am gone too.

08:47.944 --> 08:51.357
And you will never see me again.

08:52.240 --> 08:54.947
- Then I'm out.
- What?

08:55.118 --> 08:58.861
I'm done with you, with this,
the mini-dome, all of it.

08:59.039 --> 09:00.529
You can't just walk out.
We need your--

09:00.707 --> 09:03.073
My hand? I know.
My hand on the little dome

09:03.251 --> 09:06.038
so we can make pink stars and do
whatever the hell else it wants to do.

09:06.212 --> 09:09.124
This might be our only shot. Heh.

09:09.299 --> 09:11.381
And you're gonna ruin that
out of spite?

09:13.344 --> 09:15.209
I've never met someone so selfish!

09:15.388 --> 09:16.969
[WIND HOWLING]

09:19.934 --> 09:21.674
It's love, Angie.

09:22.312 --> 09:27.352
I'd rather live in here and die in here
than ever be apart from you.

09:37.827 --> 09:39.692
[ENGINE SPUTTERING]

09:40.246 --> 09:41.452
Damn it!

09:45.001 --> 09:49.335
Great, now even the cops
are getting ripped off.

09:49.756 --> 09:51.542
I need a ride!

09:56.846 --> 09:58.347
Stop your vehicle!

10:01.976 --> 10:04.228
- Are you carjacking me?
- Phil, I need a ride to Julia's.

10:04.395 --> 10:07.057
- She just got shot.
- Get in.

10:12.195 --> 10:13.856
BARBIE: Joe!
- Barbie?

10:14.030 --> 10:17.522
- Hey, get in here right now!
- Oh, my God.

10:17.700 --> 10:19.531
- Can you drive?
- I have my learner's permit,

10:19.702 --> 10:21.363
but the guy said
I didn't check my mirrors.

10:21.538 --> 10:24.029
Just help me get her in the car now.
Come on, let's sit her up.

10:24.207 --> 10:25.572
Let's go. Sit her up.

10:28.378 --> 10:30.710
Get the door! Get the door!

10:34.467 --> 10:36.048
[BARBIE GRUNTING]

10:44.936 --> 10:46.642
- Are we good?
- Yeah, we're good. Go!

11:04.122 --> 11:05.532
What the hell?

11:05.707 --> 11:08.540
Hell's right here. You want a ride?

11:10.461 --> 11:12.326
You just happen to be
in the neighborhood?

11:14.132 --> 11:16.589
It'll be nice to get a little bit of rain.

11:21.347 --> 11:22.382
You and I need to talk.

11:26.644 --> 11:31.434
- Somebody shot Julia Shumway.
- It's a perilous world we live in.

11:34.444 --> 11:35.684
I know it was you.

11:36.529 --> 11:41.023
Well, Barbie said the one word
a girl hates to hear: "No."

11:41.951 --> 11:44.203
- Where is this going, Max?
- That's up to you, Jimmy.

11:44.370 --> 11:46.577
Life's all about making
the right choices.

11:46.748 --> 11:49.785
You make the right one, you play nice,
and it's good between us.

11:49.959 --> 11:53.167
- You step out of line like Barbie did...
- Lucky for me I'm single.

11:53.338 --> 11:55.579
Oh, I'm sure there's someone
around here you care about.

11:55.757 --> 11:57.293
JUNIOR:
Dad.

12:00.136 --> 12:01.876
Go on to work, Junior.

12:02.055 --> 12:05.513
Well, look who I finally get to meet.

12:05.683 --> 12:08.925
- Junior, hi. I'm a friend of your dad's.
- Hi.

12:09.103 --> 12:14.473
Wow, you're a Rennie, all right.
Those eyes, it's like...

12:14.651 --> 12:16.687
It's like I'm looking
right at your mom.

12:17.153 --> 12:19.690
I bet you face a lot of danger
being a police officer,

12:19.864 --> 12:23.402
and I bet your dad is just constantly
worried about you, huh?

12:24.661 --> 12:26.902
- All right, that's enough, Max.
MAX: I better get going.

12:27.080 --> 12:30.243
I have some business to attend to
on Bird Island.

12:30.416 --> 12:34.534
The weather's acting up. I'm not sure
it's a great time to be on the water.

12:34.712 --> 12:36.088
Aren't you sweet to think about me?

12:36.256 --> 12:38.747
Your dad, he is so thoughtful,
to the end.

12:38.925 --> 12:43.510
I'll be at the factory later on
if you need me. Ciao.

12:55.066 --> 12:59.184
- Who was that?
- The devil.

13:03.616 --> 13:06.574
[BELLS RINGING]

13:09.247 --> 13:11.784
Julia! Julia, hey, hey, hey,
stay with me.

13:11.958 --> 13:13.448
You gotta hurry, Joe.
She's crashing.

13:13.626 --> 13:14.866
I'm working on it.

13:16.337 --> 13:17.998
[TIRES SCREECHING]

13:19.882 --> 13:22.669
- Sorry.
- You're doing great. Just get us there.

13:24.929 --> 13:28.467
JOE: It's pretty bad up there.
- It'S pretty bad back here too, Joe.

13:28.641 --> 13:33.681
I mean, it'S notjust weather.
It'S the dome. I think it'S angry at uS.

13:47.368 --> 13:50.110
I got Julia. Go ahead,
pop the trunk, plug thiS thing in.

13:50.288 --> 13:51.949
- We gonna need the juice.
- Okay.

14:10.391 --> 14:11.847
[BARBIE GRUNTING]

14:12.518 --> 14:13.553
Barbie!

14:15.772 --> 14:17.854
Let's get her inside!

14:19.108 --> 14:20.223
Put her in the second room.

14:22.820 --> 14:24.981
Yeah, right there.
So it'S a through-and-through, then?

14:25.156 --> 14:26.771
- There's no bullet to remove?
- Right.

14:26.949 --> 14:28.860
Sounds like She's taking in air
through the wound.

14:29.035 --> 14:31.947
We've gotta relieve this pressure
or else it'll crush her heart and lungS.

14:32.121 --> 14:35.079
Please, somebody,
a tree fell on our garage.

14:35.249 --> 14:37.786
My husband was inside.
He's not breathing.

14:40.797 --> 14:42.162
Go get me a piece of plastic tubing

14:42.340 --> 14:44.331
so we can relieve the pressure
in her chest here.

14:48.346 --> 14:52.134
- This place is picked clean.
- I'll make do with a pen, plastic bag.

14:52.308 --> 14:53.388
Grab some alcohol.

14:57.021 --> 15:00.809
Pen, plastic bag, the alcohol.
How do you know how to do all this?

15:00.983 --> 15:03.725
I had to chest tube
my team sergeant in Fallujah.

15:03.903 --> 15:05.234
What happened to him?

15:12.161 --> 15:14.117
[THUNDER CRASHING]

15:28.177 --> 15:30.668
I thought everybody had to
turn in their guns.

15:30.847 --> 15:32.803
I'm not everybody.

15:35.935 --> 15:37.971
Dad, what's going on?

15:39.063 --> 15:40.974
That woman Max.

15:41.566 --> 15:46.230
She's gonna take everything
I worked for and destroy it.

15:46.404 --> 15:48.395
What do you mean?

15:48.573 --> 15:53.658
Son, I've been doing my damndest
to get things back to normal,

15:53.828 --> 15:55.409
make the trains run on time.

15:56.664 --> 16:00.282
Max iS trying to fill those trains
with drugs and liquor

16:00.460 --> 16:02.951
and every kind of Sick vice
human beings can get into.

16:03.129 --> 16:05.040
She seems nice enough to me.

16:05.214 --> 16:08.047
Well, thatjust Shows you don't know
what the hell you're talking about.

16:17.852 --> 16:21.845
She's angry, Junior, at me.

16:24.650 --> 16:29.940
And She wants to hurt me
by hurting you.

16:32.867 --> 16:34.107
Then let me help you.

16:36.412 --> 16:38.243
- I can handle this.
- Dad, I can help.

16:38.414 --> 16:40.279
- Junior, no.
- I'm a man. I can do something.

16:40.458 --> 16:42.073
Junior, no!

16:52.845 --> 16:58.511
Single dad raising a kid.

17:03.523 --> 17:05.889
I did the best I could.

17:08.110 --> 17:13.901
- But you still punish me for it.
- I know I have, but not anymore.

17:15.785 --> 17:18.401
Look, son, with someone like Max...

17:19.705 --> 17:21.661
I don't know how this ends.

17:22.124 --> 17:24.911
- Dad, don't say that.
- It'S the truth.

17:38.808 --> 17:40.719
You stay in the house.

17:41.477 --> 17:45.140
Do not open the door
for anybody but me.

17:45.856 --> 17:47.471
Do you hear me?

17:59.036 --> 18:02.574
Lightning.
I wonder if that changes anything.

18:04.875 --> 18:07.082
All right, okay.

18:10.756 --> 18:12.872
MAN 1 [ON SPEAKER]:
Imagery transmission.

18:13.050 --> 18:16.133
Transmitting UHF adapter.
SA TCOM.

18:16.304 --> 18:20.673
You're kidding me. It's working again.
All right, come on, baby. Speak clearly.

18:20.850 --> 18:23.933
MAN 2: Afﬁrm.
MAN 1: It's Barbie. We've conﬁrmed it.

18:24.729 --> 18:26.811
- Barbie?
MAN 2: Yes, sir.

18:26.981 --> 18:28.812
MAN 1: We reviewed the tape
from visitors' day.

18:28.983 --> 18:31.349
There 's no question
that's Dale Barbara in there.

18:31.527 --> 18:34.815
MAN 2: Roger that.
He ’3 the one we ’ve been looking for.

18:40.036 --> 18:43.199
[BANGING ON DOOR]

18:44.540 --> 18:46.872
[BANGING CONTINUES]

18:58.679 --> 18:59.919
[SCREAMS]

19:02.099 --> 19:05.262
- What the hell are you doing?
- I could aSk you the same thing.

19:05.436 --> 19:06.767
Well, don't bother Shooting me!

19:06.937 --> 19:08.768
You're about to
get the whole town killed!

19:08.939 --> 19:12.773
- What?
- Junior, look at what it'S doing!

19:14.820 --> 19:18.062
- What iS that?
- It'S sending a message.

19:18.240 --> 19:22.529
You have to come back to the group.
It takes all of uS, or we're nothing!

19:23.037 --> 19:25.244
It'S talking to us, Junior. To you!

19:25.414 --> 19:27.450
What, so now I control the weather?

19:29.085 --> 19:33.294
ThiS thing has done a lot of crazy stuff,
but never this.

19:33.464 --> 19:35.546
Not until you turned your back on us.

19:49.355 --> 19:50.811
JOE:
Barbie?

19:53.818 --> 19:55.524
[G RU NTS]

19:55.695 --> 19:57.401
I'm good.

19:57.571 --> 19:59.527
[MACHINE BEEPING]

20:01.117 --> 20:03.483
- What's happening?
- Her heart stopped.

20:03.911 --> 20:04.946
There's too much pressure.

20:10.626 --> 20:11.991
- Unh!
- Ugh.

20:15.381 --> 20:17.087
What are you doing?

20:17.258 --> 20:19.089
Sucking out the extra air
out of her chest.

20:29.395 --> 20:31.135
We gotta ride it out
down in the Shelter!

20:31.313 --> 20:33.895
No, are you nutS?
We have to go be with Joe and Norrie!

20:34.066 --> 20:35.306
My dad said to stay here.

20:36.152 --> 20:39.394
Junior, do you want to make this right?
Then come with me.

20:39.572 --> 20:42.154
Not because I am
promising you anything,

20:42.324 --> 20:44.940
but because the dome is telling you
what you're supposed to do,

20:45.119 --> 20:46.199
to be with us.

20:47.872 --> 20:51.364
- We need you.
- You need me, Angie.

20:52.543 --> 20:56.001
Fine, I need you.

20:56.422 --> 21:00.006
Now come on!
Come on, we gotta go!

21:02.762 --> 21:04.093
Angie!

21:04.263 --> 21:05.343
Aah!

21:21.071 --> 21:22.686
See?

21:24.158 --> 21:25.898
I was right.

21:33.167 --> 21:35.032
[MACHINE BEEPING RAPIDLY]

21:51.894 --> 21:54.727
[MACHINE CHIRPS
THEN BEEPS STEADILY]

22:01.570 --> 22:03.231
It worked.

22:08.953 --> 22:13.117
- You did it.
- I had a little help, Joe.

22:23.551 --> 22:27.715
Storm'S breaking up. I gotta go now.

22:29.598 --> 22:31.099
I have to tell them.

22:31.517 --> 22:34.600
- You have to tell who?
- You saved Julia.

22:34.770 --> 22:37.011
Just like you saved me
when the dome came down.

22:40.401 --> 22:42.562
Maybe you're here to save all of us.

22:44.446 --> 22:47.313
- I don't think so, bud.
- Junior was right.

22:47.491 --> 22:48.947
